cs.GT, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.CC

The paper deals with game theory and strategies in games, which are typically categorized under cs.GT (Game Theory and Mechanism Design). The use of rational agents and the application of the results to other games suggest that it could also fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The analytical results and the use of strategies suggest that it could also be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). The study of cooperation and the emergence of strategies could also fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the application of the results to different games suggests that it could also be categorized under cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
